<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-6375] Headers are not set correctly in some situation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-6375</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If I define a route like this: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;from(&quot;&amp;lt;MyUrl&amp;gt;/test&quot;) &lt;br/&gt;
.setHeader(Exchange.HTTP_RESPONSE_CODE, simple(&quot;400&quot;)); &lt;br/&gt;
my http client get a 200 response code. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If a add something else on the route like: &lt;br/&gt;
from(&quot;&amp;lt;MyUrl&amp;gt;/test&quot;) &lt;br/&gt;
.setHeader(Exchange.HTTP_RESPONSE_CODE, simple(&quot;400&quot;)) &lt;br/&gt;
.log(&quot;400&quot;).&lt;br/&gt;
my http client get a 400 response code as expected. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;forum :&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/route-http-code-td5732728.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/route-http-code-td5732728.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
