                            <comment id="13660489" author="njiang" created="Fri, 17 May 2013 08:56:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What&apos;s your from(&quot;&amp;lt;MyUrl&amp;gt;/test&quot;)  looks like, which kind of camel component are you using?&lt;br/&gt;
After check the code of DefaultHttpBinding, I didn&apos;t found anything wrong.&lt;br/&gt;
I just did a quick test on the camel trunk, camel-2.10.x branch, I cannot reproduce the error.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13660499" author="clement tamisier" created="Fri, 17 May 2013 09:05:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am using &quot;servlet&quot; component.&lt;br/&gt;
and it works if I use setOutHeader (which is deprecated).&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ll provide soon a test case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13660580" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 17 May 2013 11:36:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah we have fixed this in the http/servlet/jetty component recently.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Though ideally the org.apache.camel.builder.ProcessorBuilder should check for OUT vs IN; currently looking into that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13660673" author="njiang" created="Fri, 17 May 2013 12:21:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue should be resolved in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-6349&quot; title=&quot;camel-restlet - Should set response correctly on Exchange depending on has out or not&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-6349&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-6349&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13660698" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 17 May 2013 13:14:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed the DSL with the setHeader / removeHeaders EIPs to work correctly on OUT or IN&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
